      "raw_text": "The proposition of putting on\ntwo trains on the Spokane Falls &\n\n\nNorthern Is in the hands of the st.\nPaul officials. The officials here\ncontemplate having one train leave\nSpokane in the morning and the\nother at night. For some time\npast this move has been contem-\nplated. The proposition, if it goes\nthrough, will be met with the\nhearty approval of the citizens who\nhave summer homes at Loon Lake.\nThe only drawback this beautiful\nlake has is railroad accomidations"
